I"‘<p>To remove directories recursively, you can use the following commnad.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">rm</span> <span class="nt">-rf</span> <span class="sb">`</span>find <span class="nb">.</span> <span class="nt">-type</span> d <span class="nt">-name</span> .svn<span class="sb">`</span>  </code></pre></figure>

<p>‚Äú- type d‚Äù is used for directories. Without it you can delete files also.</p>

